ile app screenshot 07" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0125" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0125-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/eventespressoapps-teaser" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/eventespressoapps-teaser-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/eventespressoapps-thumb" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/eventespressoapps-thumb-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17021">Preview the upcoming Event Espresso mobile ticketing app (for iPhone and Android)</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 18:02:36 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:16;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Matt: Tim Ferriss On Facebook, Twitter And Building A Huge Web Brand";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=37964";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://ma.tt/2011/04/tf-on-wp/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1387:"<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>I think there’s a difference between having a bestselling book–meaning through marketing, PR and buying that first wave of customers–and writing a bestselling book. The second implies that the product propels itself to the best seller list. That’s not to say that I’m Tolstoy or the best writer, but I used Facebook and Twitter more for feed back as I was creating and refining the book than for the actual marketing itself. My main online tool for priming the pump for the launch of the book was the blog. That was the heartbeat and the nexus for all the different tools that I use.</p></blockquote></div>\n<p>Via <a href="http://blogs.forbes.com/stevenbertoni/2011/04/14/tim-ferriss-on-facebook-twitter-and-building-a-huge-web-brand/">Tim Ferriss On Facebook, Twitter And Building A Huge Web Brand &#8211; Steven Bertoni &#8211; Money Talks &#8211; Forbes</a>. I also liked this quote:</p>\n<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>SB: How can a magazine catch up to the Web?</p>\n<p>TF: If I worked for a magazine that’s very behind the times, I wouldn’t reinvent the wheel. I’d use WordPress as a content management system which has very good SEO out of the box. Companies spend so much time trying to develop something proprietary it’s ridiculous–you have thousands of people already working on WordPress.</p></blockquote></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 17:32:37 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:17;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/SvUsP_3sxZI/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-date-moves-to-the-fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2257:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17017" title="WordCamp Atlanta 2011 logo (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampatlantalogo-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="239" /></a></p><p>WordCamp Atlanta 2011 was <a title="WordCamp Atlanta is officially scheduled for May 6th and 7th" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-may-6-7">initially scheduled</a> for the beginning of May. Due to the organization team wanting to ensure a larger event than 2010, the event has been pushed back to a yet-to-be announced date this fall.</p><p>Not much was said in the <a title="WordCamp Atlanta date announcement" href="http://atlantawordcamp.com/2011/04/update-wordcamp-atlanta-2011-is-moving-to-fall-2011/">announcement</a>, but organizer Tessa Horehled did share some of their plans for the extra time before this year&#8217;s event:</p><blockquote><p>This year’s event is going to be pushed back to Fall so we can ensure this year’s event even bigger and better than last year, by bringing more great leaders from the Atlanta WordCamp community into the fold and securing a brand new venue which we hope to announce in the coming months.</p></blockquote><p>We&#8217;ll keep an eye out and notify you when WordCamp Atlanta 2011&#8242;s date is firmed up. Until then, who&#8217;s looking forward to the next event in Atlanta?</p><p>I attended last year&#8217;s event, which was fantastic, and <a title="Parent/child theme presentation on Slideshare" href="http://www.slideshare.net/ryanimel/speeding-up-site-development-with-parent-and-child-themes">presented on child themes</a>. I&#8217;m looking forward to attending this year, though I will probably be more focused on <a title="WPCandy covers WordCamps" href="http://wpcandy.com/on/wordcamp">covering WordCamp</a> than I will be trying to present on a particular topic. Who has attended in the past that will be going again this year?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016">WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall </a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 16:43:10 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b: