(130, 1, '2011-04-19 17:31:25', '2011-04-19 17:31:25', 'Terry Southern was born on May 1, 1924, in Alvarado, Texas and moved to the Dallas area at the age of 5. His formative years in Texas influenced him greatly, particularly his experiences with African American culture. At age 12, he discovered Edgar Allen Poe''s The Narrative of A. Gordon Pym, decided it “didn''t go far enough,” and rewrote it. In 1942, he attended SMU in Dallas, and joined the army soon after the War broke out. After serving in England and Normandy, he returned to the US in 1946 and enrolled in the "Great Books" program at Northwestern, where he received his degree in English. ', 'Texas, College and War 1924 - 1944', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'texas-college-and-war-1924-1944', '', '', '2011-04-19 17:31:25', '2011-04-19 17:31:25', '', 0, 'http://dev.reddirtcollective.com/?p=130', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2011-04-19 17:31:18', '2011-04-19 17:31:18', 'Terry Southern was born on May 1, 1924, in Alvarado, Texas and moved to the Dallas area at the age of 5. His formative years in Texas influenced him greatly, particularly his experiences with African American culture. At age 12, he discovered Edgar Allen Poe''s The Narrative of A. Gordon Pym, decided it “didn''t go far enough,” and rewrote it. In 1942, he attended SMU in Dallas, and joined the army soon after the War broke out. After serving in England and Normandy, he returned to the US in 1946 and enrolled in the "Great Books" program at Northwestern, where he received his degree in English. ', 'Texas, College and War 1924 - 1944', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '130-revision', '', '', '2011-04-19 17:31:18', '2011-04-19 17:31:18', '', 130, 'http://dev.reddirtcollective.com/?p=131', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(132, 1, '2011-04-19 17:32:54', '2011-04-19 17:32:54', 'Southern  studied abroad under the G.I. Bill, and was exposed to lectures by Sartre and Camus, among other Existentialists. This was the era of be-bop''s explosion, and in Paris he frequented the jazz clubs with friends, saw European films, and made trips to Pamplona to run with the bulls. His first published work emerged in this period, and he began exhibiting a “hipster” persona that would stay with him for much of his life. He became friends with numerous influential authors and intellectuals of this period, many of whom became lifelong friends. On a ship to France he met a model from Tennessee, Pud Gadiot, and married her.', 'Expatriation 1948 - 1952', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expatriation-1948-1952', '', '', '2011-04-19 17:32:54', '2011-04-19 17:32:54', '', 0, 'http://dev.reddirtcollective.com/?p=132', 0, 'post', '', 0),
